         <div type="translation">
            <ab>OIM 19317, recto: (1) Amenothes son of Parates has brought 2 1/2 silver [kite] in the name of Tamounis(?), [whose(?) south is] (2) the tomb of kalasiris, north is the tomb of Mnt-htp, (3) east is the path, west is [the] mountain, which completes the neighbors of (4) the tomb which is above ... [...] has written Petemestous son of (5) Poulemis(?) on Egyptian year 24, [Mecheir(?)] day 30 of pharaoh (6) Ptolemy (II) son of Ptolemy, with (7) Ptolemy his son.</ab>
